Can you help me make a start programming it?

Certainly! I would be more than happy to assist you in getting started with programming your car script. Please let me know which programming language you would like to use for the script, and I can provide you with some initial guidance and resources to help you begin the development process.
Luau

Great choice! LuaU is the primary scripting language used in Roblox. To get started with programming your car script in LuaU, I recommend familiarizing yourself with the basics of Lua programming first, as LuaU is an extension of Lua. You can find helpful resources and tutorials on the Lua website (https://www.lua.org/docs.html) as well as the Roblox Developer Hub (https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/learn-roblox).

For specific guidance on creating a car script, there are also community resources and forums where you can find code samples and examples. The Roblox Developer Forum (https://devforum.roblox.com/) and the Roblox Wiki (https://roblox.fandom.com/wiki/Roblox_Wiki) are great places to explore and seek assistance from fellow developers.

If you need any further assistance or have any specific questions during your programming journey, feel free to ask!
Write some basic code for it

Certainly! Here's a simple example of a LuaU car script to help you get started:

```lua
local car = script.Parent -- Assuming the script is placed inside the car model

local driverSeat = car:WaitForChild("DriverSeat") -- The seat the player will sit in
local carSpeed = 50 -- The speed at which the car will move

local function moveCar()
    local humanoid = driverSeat.Occupant -- Get the occupant of the driver seat
    if humanoid then
        local rootPart = humanoid.RootPart -- Get the RootPart of the player
        car:SetPrimaryPartCFrame(rootPart.CFrame) -- Move the car based on player's position
        car:SetPrimaryPartCFrame(car:GetPrimaryPartCFrame() * CFrame.new(0, 0, -carSpeed)) -- Move the car forward
    end
end

driverSeat:GetPropertyChangedSignal("Occupant"):Connect(moveCar) -- Call move
